<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="283" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[130,777,1156,1378]" box="[132,232,1156,1182]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[130,777,1156,1378]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">
Photographs and original drawings of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[543,639,1188,1214]" class="Asteroidea" family="Asterinidae" genus="Parvulastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="exigua">
<emphasis box="[543,639,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">A. exigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[646,737,1189,1215]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">syntypes</typeStatus>
are presented in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jangoux" box="[271,487,1221,1247]" firstAuthor="Jangoux" page="228" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" pagination="213 - 252" refId="ref44008" refString="JANGOUX M. 2021. - The asteroid species of Lamarck (Echinodermata: Asteroidea). Zoosystema 43 (13): 213 - 252. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / zoosystema 2021 v 43 a 13. http: // zoosystema. com / 43 / 13" type="journal article" year="2021">Jangoux (2021: 228</bibRefCitation>
fig.15).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[130,777,1156,1378]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">
Due to wrong information (presumed loss of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[629,724,1254,1280]" class="Asteroidea" family="Asterinidae" genus="Parvulastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="exigua">
<emphasis box="[629,724,1254,1280]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">A. exigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type specimens), 
<bibRefCitation author="Dartnall" box="[270,447,1286,1313]" firstAuthor="Dartnall" pageId="26" pageNumber="283" pagination="41 - 49" refId="ref43449" refString="DARTNALL A. J. 1971. - Australian sea stars of the genus Patiriella (Asteroidea, Asterinidae). Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales 96: 41 - 49. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 34947978" type="journal article" year="1971">Dartnall (1971)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus box="[603,690,1287,1313]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">neotype</typeStatus>
for the species. The 
<typeStatus box="[269,355,1319,1345]" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">neotype</typeStatus>
is from False Bay (
<collectingCountry box="[559,699,1319,1346]" name="South Africa" pageId="26" pageNumber="283">South Africa</collectingCountry>
) and is kept in the TMH (ref. TMH 508).
</paragraph>
